SIMPLE: thievish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thievish
<hw>Thiev"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Given to stealing;
addicted to theft; <as>as, a <ex>thievish</ex> boy, a <ex>thievish</ex>
magpie</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Like a thief; acting by stealth; sly;
secret.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Time's <qex>thievish</qex> progress to eternity.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Partaking of the nature of theft; accomplished by
stealing; dishonest; <as>as, a <ex>thievish</ex>
practice</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Or with a base and biosterous sword enforce⟦br⟧
A <qex>thievish</qex> living on the common road.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Thiev"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Thiev"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thigh</ent>⟦br⟧
